The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter FOUR people died due to Covid-19 complications on Tuesday while 122 new infections were recorded countrywide. Bulawayo and Manicaland provinces recorded a death each while two people succumbed to the deadly pandemic in Mashonaland East. <img class="alignnone wp-image-509367 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/08/dead-body-corona.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/08/dead-body-corona.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/08/dead-body-corona-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Since the country recorded its first Covid-19 case in March, 326 have succumbed to the virus while 12 544 infections have been recorded. Local transmissions still dominate the country’s Covid-19 cases as 105 individuals tested positive within the country on Tuesday while 17 infections were recorded from returning residents coming from South Africa. The Covid-19 active cases have also increased to 2059 as the country’s weekly positivity rate increased to an average of 140 cases. <img class="alignnone wp-image-492057 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Coronavirus-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Coronavirus-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Coronavirus-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Covid-19 cases are increasing at a time when the country and the world is in the festive season, a period of merry making and increased travelling. Despite the festive season mood, members of the public have been urged to observe Covid-19 prevention measures and stick to laid down regulations. <img class="alignnone wp-image-490991 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/corona12.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/corona12.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/corona12-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Citizens are encouraged to properly wear their masks, observe social distancing while minimising on unnecessary gatherings and travelling.